  "body": "Bright, Mediterranean meal-prep bowl with lemon-tahini chicken, roasted vegetables, and brown rice. It reheats well, stays juicy, and feels fresh rather than heavy.\n\nPrep time: 40 minutes\nEquipment: large baking tray, medium saucepan with lid, large skillet, mixing bowl, whisk, knife, cutting board, meal-prep containers.\n\n1. Heat the oven to 220°C. Toss {zucchini}, {red bell pepper}, {red onion}, and {cherry tomatoes} with half of {olive oil}, {dried oregano}, salt, and pepper on a baking tray. Roast for **18-20 min**, stirring once halfway, until the edges start to caramelize.\n2. While the vegetables roast, rinse {brown rice dry} and cook it in plenty of lightly salted water for **25-30 min**, until tender. Drain well and keep covered.\n3. Pat {chicken breast raw} dry and season with salt and pepper. Heat the remaining {olive oil} in a skillet over medium-high heat for **1 min**, then sear the chicken for **4-5 min per side** until golden and cooked through. Rest for **5 min** before slicing.\n4. Whisk {tahini}, the juice of {lemon}, and minced {garlic} with a splash of water until smooth and pourable; season with salt and pepper.\n5. Divide the rice, roasted vegetables, and sliced chicken between containers. Spoon the sauce over the top, cool completely, then seal.\n\nStorage: keep in the fridge for up to 3 days. Reheat **2-3 min** in the microwave, stirring once halfway. Tip: if the bowl looks a little dry after reheating, add a small splash of water and an extra squeeze of lemon to wake it back up."
